{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, when we increase the number of AI agents engaged in search, the LLMs are more likely to gravitate toward the medium-value option.",
    "When eliciting agents' motivations, we find that their responses suggest herding behaviors due to social conformity-a mechanism absent from the original theory of Hoelzemann et al. (2024).",
    "Second, we uncover additional boundary conditions for the streetlight effect.",
    "For instance, when we introduce payoff rivalry, AI agents no longer herd around the safe option for fear of splitting the rewards.",
    "We also document the theory's robustness to several assumptions."
  ]
}